Operatives of Lagos State Police Command have arrested one Kazeem Mustapha along Madoti Estate Fin-Niger, Satellite town in Lagos State for killing an apprentice after a minor misunderstanding over N500. According to police spokesperson, Bala Elkana, a Deputy Superintendent of Police the incident happened on February 25,2020  when one Rafiu Dauda  of No 36 Alebiosu Street Ijegun, Satellite town reported at Elemoro Police Station that his apprentice Afeez Oluwole, 33 years old, was stabbed on the right chest with broken bottle by one Kazeem Mustapha ‘m’ along Madoti Estate Fin-Niger, Satellite town, due to a minor misunderstanding over N500. He said Afeez Oluwole was rushed to Holy Family Hospital where he later died. “The corpse was deposited at the mortuary for postmortem examination. However, the suspect was arrested and He will be charged to Court soon.’’ In a similar development, he said a girl was arrested over the death of a 47 years old woman in Lagos. The incident happened on February 28,2020  at about 1000hrs when one Afeez Oloande, of No. 2 Ado Road, Ajah Lekki and one Femi Olasunde  reported at Elemero Police Station that one Opeyemi Abidemi, 20 years old had a fight with one Abosede Bello, 47 years old.  